le Ages, Michael was regarded as captain of the heavenly host (see Revelation 12:7–9), symbol of the Church Militant, and patron of soldiers. He was often depicted bearing a flaming sword. The name is also borne by a Persian prince and ally of Belshazzar mentioned in the Book of Daniel. Since the early 1900s it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names in the English-speaking world.  See also  Michal ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Michael Folkroy was born in 1260, in Houndstone, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, his father, Fulcherius Folkeroy, was 40 and his mother, Mrs. Fulcherius Folkeroy, was 34. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Michael Folkroy."},"et":{"1260–":"1260–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1282–Male":"1282–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1226–Female":"1226–Surnud","1226":"1226","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1282":"1282","       1282":"1282","Houndstone, Somerset, England":"Houndstone, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1260–":"1260–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1282–Male":"1282–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1226–Female":"1226–Kuollut","1226":"1226","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1282":"1282","       1282":"1282","Houndstone, Somerset, England":"Houndstone, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1260–":"1260–Décédé","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1282–Male":"1282–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1226–Female":"1226–Décédée","1226":"1226","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1282":"1282","       1282":"1282","Houndstone, Somerset, England":"Houndstone, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Devonshire, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Michael Folkroy est né en 1260, à Houndstone, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Fulcherius Folkeroy, avait 40 ans et